140.speaker: PENGUIN
140.character: 僕、好きなペンギンさんが居るんだ
140.definition: I have a penguin that I like.

141.speaker: LLAMA
141.character: すみません、抹茶パフェください
141.definition: Excuse me. Could I get a green tea parfait?

142.speaker: LLAMA
142.definition: And? I have a penguin that I like—

143.speaker: LLAMA
143.character: すみません、やっぱりいちごパフェにしてくれますか
143.definition: Excuse me, could you change that to a strawberry parfait?

144.speaker: PENGUIN
144.definition: Hey! Are you even listening?! Hello!

145.speaker: PANDA
145.character: しろくま君　いつもの
145.definition: Could I get the usual, Polar Bear?

146.speaker: POLAR BEAR
146.character: お待ち遠様　竹大盛りね
146.definition: There you go. A large serving of bamboo.

148.speaker: POLAR BEAR
148.definition: Should we do it? What? A cherry blossom viewing party.

153.speaker: PENGUIN
153.character: 今年も綺麗に咲いたね
153.definition: They blossomed amazingly again this year.

154.speaker: PANDA
154.definition: I wonder what we should do for snacks...

155.speaker: PENGUIN
155.definition: What an unromantic thing to say.

156.speaker: PENGUIN
156.character: 桜は綺麗だなって話してるんだから
156.definition: We're talking about how pretty the cherry blossoms are. Hey, do you have any snacks? You're not listening at all. Oh, well.

157.speaker: LLAMA
157.character: 花弁って食べられますかね
157.definition: I wonder if the cherry blossoms are edible.

158.speaker: PENGUIN
158.character: もう一人情緒ないのがいるよ
158.definition: And another one who doesn't get it.

159.speaker: PENGUIN
159.character: ラマさんは草が食べられるなら　食べられるんじゃない？
159.definition: You probably could, considering you eat grass, as well.

160.speaker: PANDA
160.definition: Hey, do you have any bamboo?

162.speaker: POLAR BEAR
162.character: お弁当なら持って来たよ
162.definition: I packed a lunch for us.

163.speaker: PANDA
163.definition: You're amazing, Polar Bear! I'm... going to... run some errands...

166.speaker: SLOTH
166.character: 何か乾き物買ってくる
166.definition: a drink... at the... convenience store— It's all right, we have enough here.

167.speaker: SLOTH
167.definition: It's just right over there... I'll be... right back...

171.speaker: PENGUIN
171.character: こんなに綺麗なのに、すぐに散っちゃうんだから
171.definition: They're so beautiful, but they fall so quickly.

172.speaker: PENGUIN
172.definition: It's all so fleeting. This is a new recipe I tried. Oh! It looks delicious! Thank you for the food! Hey! Stop eating and let's do something

173.speaker: PENGUIN
173.character: もっとお花見らしいことしようよ
173.definition: more fitting for a cherry blossom viewing party. More fitting for a cherry blossom viewing party? Like singing.

174.speaker: PANDA
174.definition: I'm terrible at singing. Same here.

182.speaker: PANDA
182.definition: Mr. Penguin is sleeping. That's not it! I'm just got tired of your stupid puns and fell over!

183.speaker: POLAR BEAR
183.character: ひどいなぁ、ペンギンさん
183.definition: Well, that was rude, Mr. Penguin.

184.speaker: PENGUIN
184.definition: You know there's more to do at these events! How about impersonations?!

185.speaker: PENGUIN
185.character: わ～～名倉さんの物真似でしょう
185.definition: That's totally an impersonation of Mr. Nagura!

186.speaker: LLAMA
186.definition: I'm just... eating. We're lacking something. I know! Polar Bear! Lift me up to that tree there! I'll fly! I don't think that's a good idea.

187.speaker: PENGUIN
187.definition: Why are you trying to stop me?! Then you do it, Panda!

188.speaker: PENGUIN
188.character: ほら、僕を木の上に乗せて
188.definition: Come on! Lift me up into the tree! I'm Llama.

189.speaker: SASAKO
189.definition: He appears to be rather drunk. I think he drank too much. Wow, that's amazing!

190.speaker: PANDA
190.character: お花見らしくなってきたよ、ペンギンさん
190.definition: It's like a real cherry blossom viewing party! Mr. Penguin?

192.speaker: SASAKO
192.definition: He's totally knocked out. Hey! Don't sleep!

193.speaker: PANDA
193.definition: We're awake. Young penguins these days just don't get it!

194.speaker: PENGUIN
194.character: 可愛いだけじゃダメなんだよ
194.definition: It's not just about being cute! Am I right?!

198.speaker: PENGUIN
198.character: 吉崎さん、目の周りにあざがあるよ
198.definition: Oh no! You have bruises around your eyes, Mr. Yoshizaki!

199.speaker: PENGUIN
199.character: 誰かに殴られたよ？大丈夫？
199.definition: Did someone hit you? Are you okay?! This is getting annoying.

200.speaker: PENGUIN
200.definition: Hey, Mr. Nagura. Are you listening?

203.speaker: PENGUIN
203.character: 好きなペンギンがいるんだよ
203.definition: I have a penguin that I like.

204.speaker: PENGUIN
204.character: パン屋のバイトのペンコさんっていうんだけど
204.definition: Her name is Miss Penko and she works at the bakery part-time.

206.speaker: PENGUIN
206.character: ペンコさん　一生僕と同じ魚を食べてください！
206.definition: Please share the same fish with me for as long as we both live, Miss Penko!

209.speaker: POLAR BEAR
209.character: もう面白いから、見ていいよ
209.definition: This is rather amusing, so I'll just watch. Jeez! W-Will you listen to what I have to say?

210.speaker: PANDA
210.definition: What? I wrote a poem about Miss Penko. Really? How does it go?

214.speaker: PENGUIN
214.character: ペンコさんが魚を食べる

215.speaker: PENGUIN
215.character: どうですか、ペンコさん
215.definition: What do you think, Miss Penko?

217.speaker: POLAR BEAR
217.character: ペンギンさん、ちょっとペンコさんと散歩してきたら、
217.definition: Why don't you go on a walk with Miss Penko, Mr. Penguin?

219.speaker: PENGUIN
219.character: じゃ、行こうか、ペンコさん

222.speaker: PENGUIN
222.character: 二人きりのロマンチックな夜だね
222.definition: It'll be a romantic evening with just the two of us.

223.speaker: PANDA
223.character: いろいろ違ってる気がするよ
223.definition: I can't help but feel there's a lot wrong with this.

224.speaker: PENGUIN
224.character: いつまでもこうして歩いていたいなぁ
224.definition: I wish we could walk like this forever.

225.speaker: PANDA
225.definition: I want to go home. Miss Penko, will you go out with—  What?! Where did you come from, Mr. Yoshizaki?!

227.speaker: PENGUIN
227.character: ペンコさん、どこ！ペンコさん！
227.definition: Miss Penko, where did you go?! Miss Penko!

230.speaker: SLOTH
230.character: コンビニ行ってきたよ
230.definition: I went... to the convenience store... No one's... here...

231.speaker: POLAR BEAR
231.definition: The night blossoms are pretty, too.

232.speaker: PANDA
232.character: 昨日はびっくりしたね

234.speaker: PANDA
234.character: ペンギンさんって酒癖悪いね
234.definition: Mr. Penguin doesn't handle  alcohol very well.

236.speaker: PENGUIN
236.definition: My head is pounding for some reason.

237.speaker: PANDA
237.character: あれ　それでペンコさんのパン屋さんで買ったの
237.definition: Oh, did you buy that from the bakery Miss Penko works at?

238.speaker: PENGUIN
238.definition: What?! How do you know about that?!

240.speaker: PENGUIN
240.character: なんで僕のポエムを　なんで知ってるの
240.definition: How do you know about my poem?! Why do you know about it?!

241.speaker: PANDA
241.character: ペンコさん　一生僕と同じ魚を食べてください
241.definition: "Please share the same fish with me for as long as we both live, Miss Penko!"

242.speaker: PENGUIN
242.character: 僕が考えてるプロポーズの言葉！！
242.definition: The words I was going to use for my proposal!

243.speaker: PENGUIN
243.definition: How do you know about that?!

245.speaker: PENGUIN
245.character: 誰にも話してないのに

248.speaker: LLAMA
248.character: ペンコさんが魚を食べる
248.definition: "Miss Penko eats fish." Knock it off!

249.speaker: PANDA
249.character: ペンギンさんペンギンさん

250.speaker: PANDA
250.definition: Did you have some plastic surgery done?

252.speaker: PENGUIN
252.character: 逆に聞くけど、何でそう思った？
252.definition: But let me ask, why did you think that?

253.speaker: PANDA
253.character: じゃ僕も逆に聞くけど
253.definition: But now let me ask, what do you think {\i1}nata de coco{\i0} is made from? How did you think to ask that?

254.speaker: PENGUIN
254.character: しろくま君　纏めて
254.definition: Could you wrap this up, Polar Bear?

255.speaker: POLAR BEAR
255.character: 次回のしろくまカフェは

256.speaker: POLAR BEAR
256.character: 実写版でお送りします　お楽しみに
256.definition: will be presented in live-action. Enjoy!

257.speaker: PENGUIN
257.character: 送らないよ　アニメだよ
257.definition: No, it won't! It'll be animated.
